    <item>
      <title>Devouring lovers and a Christmas market</title>
      <link>https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00005-devouring_lovers_and_a_christmas_market/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Dec 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>GIGKOMUSIC@gmail.com (GIGKO)</author>
      <guid>https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00005-devouring_lovers_and_a_christmas_market/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Today is the first day in December and I went outside to visit the Hamburger Bahnhof Gallery and the WeihnachtsZauber Gendarmenmarkt Christmas Market.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &amp;ldquo;Devouring Lovers&amp;rdquo; exhibition by Eva Fàbregas is now going on in Hamburger Bahnhof Gallery and here are some photos I shot there today.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00005-devouring_lovers_and_a_christmas_market/feature.jpg" />
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Dynamic programming</title>
      <link>https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00004-dynamic_programming/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Nov 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>GIGKOMUSIC@gmail.com (GIGKO)</author>
      <guid>https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00004-dynamic_programming/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The essential idea of dynamic programming is to save the result for future use.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For example, if I have already know 1+2+3 equals 6 and saved the result at a place, then when I have to calculate 1+2+3+4, I just have to calculate 6+4 instead of going from scratch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00004-dynamic_programming/feature.jpg" />
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Who should be the manager</title>
      <link>https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00003-who_should_be_the_manager/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Nov 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>GIGKOMUSIC@gmail.com (GIGKO)</author>
      <guid>https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00003-who_should_be_the_manager/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I watched &amp;ldquo;Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse&amp;rdquo; today. It is an entertaining film. Excellent video effects, and, especially, the surprising but wonderful combination of various versions of spider-men based on the Spider-Verse theory. I was not surprised to find that the audience could not help to shout &amp;ldquo;WOW&amp;rdquo; when different kinds of spider-men, say, Lego spider-man, real world spider-man, and so on, showed rightly on the big screen.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://GIGKOMUSIC.github.io/posts/00003-who_should_be_the_manager/feature.jpg" />
    </item>
    
